    {
      "claim": "Points M and B lie on line AB, and points N and C lie on lines AB and AC respectively; moreover, MB = OB and NB = OB.",
      "reasoning": "Because M lies on the circle centered at O through B, we have OM = OB. Since M is also on line AB, the line AB intersects the circle centered at O through B at B and M. Similarly, N lies on the circle centered at O through B, so ON = OB. The equal-radius information will be used later to compare the geometry around R.",
