    {
      "claim": "The line RP is the radical axis of circles O1 and O2.",
      "reasoning": "Since P lies on both circles O1 and O2, it has equal power with respect to both circles, and R also lies on both circles by construction. Therefore the common chord through the two intersection points of the circles is the line RP, which is the radical axis.",
      "facts_used": ["definition of radical axis", "step 4"]
