    {
      "claim": "The radical axis of circles O1 and O2 is the line BC.",
      "reasoning": "The circles O1 = (BMR) and O2 = (CNR) are constructed so that the configuration is symmetric with respect to the geometry determined by the midpoint O of BC and the angle-bisector point R. The angle-bisector conditions imply that the signed powers of B and C with respect to these circles are equal, so B and C have equal power to both circles; hence B and C lie on the radical axis. Therefore the radical axis is the line through B and C, namely BC.",
